The U.S. Securities and ExchangeCommission said it charged a managing director ofMerrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner and Smith Ltd in London withmasterminding "a massive insider trading scheme."    Nahum Vaskevitch, managing director of the Mergers andAcquisitions Department of the broker's London office, wascharged in a civil complaint by the SEC filed in ManhattanFederal Court.    The complaint said Vaskevitch leaked information about 12companies involved in a merger or acquisition which resulted inmore than four mln dlrs in profit for himself and othersinvolved in the scheme.    Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner and Smith is a subsidiary ofMerrill Lynch and Co Inc. Reuter&#3;